<subSubSection id="7560EBE3F94A9393835C0F77910F4BDB" pageId="5" pageNumber="32" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="BA78AFD767A8E17BCEE1B55AEDBCB29A" pageId="5" pageNumber="32">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7E0AB30B299042017D2BEDEB8F52955A" pageId="5" pageNumber="32">
This speciesis here recorded from Iran for the first time, based on one apterous male.Hamedan province: Hamedan, Qahavand, from 
<taxonomicName id="A71A312ED264F0E39BA8F3CA7C9520A7" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Salvia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Salvia nemorosa" order="Lamiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nemorosa">Salvia nemorosa</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="421EC5000B78C46387A84EA86F3EC0A5" genus="Lamiaceae" lsidName="Lamiaceae" pageId="5" pageNumber="32" rank="genus">Lamiaceae</taxonomicName>
), 20.viii.2010, coll. M. Mirab-balou (in ZJUH). The male of this speciesis easily distinguished from other species of 
<taxonomicName id="41A97D6709BA0CD0534D8823B7829308" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Chirothrips" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Chirothrips" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Chirothrips</taxonomicName>
by having small pore plates on abdominal sternite III and IV.
</paragraph>
